<exploration xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="PA-trig-finding-angles">

	<statement>
		<p>
			Consider a right triangle that has one leg of length <m>3</m> and another leg of length <m>\sqrt{3}</m>.  Let <m>\theta</m> be the angle that lies opposite the shorter leg.  
		</p>

		<ol label="a.">
			<li>
				<p>
					Sketch a labeled picture of the triangle.
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>
					What is the exact length of the triangle's hypotenuse?
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>
					What is the exact value of <m>\sin(\theta)</m>?
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>
					Rewrite your equation from (b) using the arcsine function in the form <m>\arcsin(\Box) = \Delta</m>, where <m>\Box</m> and <m>\Delta</m> are numerical values.
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>
					What special angle from the unit circle is <m>\theta</m>?
				</p>
			</li>
		</ol>
	</statement>

</exploration>